Package maze

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Graph
    A graph is an ordered set of vertices, linked by distances to one another.
    InterfaceableMaze
    This interface describes a maze which can be modified by an interface.
    Vertex
    A vertex is the atomic unit used to describe a graph.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Box
    This abstract class implements a graph's vertex.
    BridgeBox
    NOT IMPLEMENTED YET, REQUIRES INTERNAL MODIFICATIONS.
    EmptyBox
    Basic box with maximum practicability.
    Maze
    Implements the InterfaceableMaze and Graph interfaces.
    StairsBox
    NOT IMPLEMENTED YET, REQUIRES INTERNAL MODIFICATIONS.
    WallBox
    Basic box with infinite practicability.
    WaterBox
    Box of variable practicability finite if shallow, infinite if deep.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BoxFlag
    This enumerated type describes a set of flags carried by a Box instance.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InvalidBoxArgumentsException
    Signals that a box could not be built because of an incorrect number of arguments.
    MazeException
    Signals the maze has encountered an issue of some sort.
    MazeOutOfBoundsException
    Signals an attempt to reach a box outside the maze.
    NullBoxException
    Signals en attempt to reach coordinates where there is no box.
    ReadingException
    Signals an error occured while reading a maze from a stream.
    UnexpectedBoxTypeException
    Signals a box type was not found.
